South Korea April LNG Imports Jump 6.3%; Average Price Rose

-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 
2011-05-15T00:39:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/south-korea-april-lng-imports-jump-6-3-average-price-rose-1-.html
South Korea , the world’s second-
largest buyer of liquefied natural gas, increased imports of the
fuel in April by 6.3 percent from a year earlier, according to
customs data.  The Asian nation bought 2.38 million metric tons of the
cleaner-burning fuel last month, from 2.24 million tons in April
2010, data posted on the Korea Customs Service’s  website  showed
today. The country paid $1.50 billion, or $629.0 a ton, compared
with $1.27 billion, or $567.36 a ton, a year earlier, the data
showed.  South Korea, which imports almost all its natural gas
needs, purchased 113,583 tons in the spot market for $561.64 a
ton from  Trinidad & Tobago , according to the data.  Korea Gas Corp. (036460) ’s natural gas sales volume in April rose
4.6 percent on the year to 2.76 million metric tons, according
to a regulatory filing by the state-run utility on May 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sungwoo Park in Seoul at 
 spark47@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
